#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:5
msgid "Bug Reporting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:7
msgid ""
"All bugs should be filed in the GitHub `main <https://github.com/emscripten-"
"core/emscripten>`_ Emscripten repository `Issue Tracker <https://github.com/"
"emscripten-core/emscripten/issues?state=open>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:11
msgid "Please supply as much relevant information as possible, including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:13
msgid "Original source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:14
msgid "Generated bitcode (**.bc**, **.o** or **.ll**)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:15
msgid ""
"Environment information — including *emcc* and *clang* versions (as reported "
"by ``emcc -v``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:16
msgid "Error symptoms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:17
msgid "Proposed solutions, ideally with a pull request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:19
msgid ""
"Compile with ``EMCC_DEBUG=1`` and grab the **/tmp/emscripten_temp/emcc-\\*** "
"files (these include the bitcode and JavaScript in several stages). Note "
"that the **emscripten_temp** directory should be emptied manually first, so "
"it only contains new content!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:26
msgid "LLVM, wasm-ld, clang, Binaryen bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:28
msgid ""
"If uncertain, bugs can always be posted to the `main repository <https://"
"github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten>`_. But if you are sure a bug is in an "
"upstream project, you can file it there:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:32
msgid ""
"`LLVM bug tracker <https://bugs.llvm.org/>`_ . For most issues use the "
"\"libraries\" product and the \"Backend: WebAssembly\" component. For wasm-"
"ld issues, use \"lld\" and \"wasm\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:35
msgid ""
"`Binaryen bug tracker <https://github.com/WebAssembly/binaryen/issues>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:37
msgid "Pull requests must (of course) go to the proper repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:43
msgid "Site and documentation bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:45
msgid ""
"Documentation (site) bugs should be filed in the same `Issue Tracker "
"<https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues?state=open>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:48
msgid "Include relevant information including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:50
msgid "The URL and title of the affected page(s)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:51
msgid "A description of the problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:52
msgid "Suggestions for a possible solution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/bug_reports.rst:54
msgid ""
"The `Page bug <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues/new?"
"title=Bug%20in%20page:How%20to%20Report%20Bugs%20%28under-"
"construction%29%20&body=REPLACE%20THIS%20TEXT%20WITH%20BUG%20DESCRIPTION%20%0A%0AURL:"
"%20../../docs/site/Bug-Reports&labels=bug>`_ link on the bottom-right of "
"every page opens the Issue Tracker pre-seeded with the current page URL and "
"title."
msgstr ""
